## Findings
- Goose is an open-source AI agent for developers, written in Rust.
- Supports 15+ LLM providers and MCP (Model Context Protocol).
- Features a desktop app, CLI, and API.
- Part of the Agentic AI Foundation (AAIF), previously by Block.
- Integrated with ACP (Agent Context Protocol) for using existing subscriptions.
- Architecture: Interface (CLI/Desktop) -> Agent (Core Logic) -> Extensions (Tools/MCP).

